misconceptions.inferred_category_name: Implicit assumption that N is always at least 1 (unchecked empty input case)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes there will always be at least one student, so it is safe to access names[n - 1] and scores[n - 1] without checking n.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: In Java, arrays of length 0 are valid, but any access (including index -1 when n == 0) throws an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException. Programs that accept user-provided N should validate N before indexing based on it.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: Runtime exception (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException) when the user enters 0 (or a negative value causing NegativeArraySizeException earlier).
